Here are my motions in better format:

Motion One: Resolved: Executive Director Bill Hall is hereby Censured
and Reprimanded for failing to provide documents at all pertaining to
the Pension/Profit Sharing Plan.

Motion Two: In as much as Bobby Fischer is a USCf member by delegate
mandate and 1992 resolution submitted by Joe Lux, he isc to be
assigned as USCF ID number and his name and last rating is to be
posted on the MSA section of the website as a USCF member.

Motion Three: Resolved: Grandmaster Larry Evans is hereby reinstated
as a regular monthy columnis in Chess Life magazine and his regular
monthly question and answer column is hereby restored and the editor
of Chess Life is hereby specifically ordered and directed to publish
said monthly column.

Motion Four: Resolved: It shall be the policy of the USCF to rate all
world chess championship events and all top level super-grandmaster
events and the ratings department is hereby directed to rate the 2004
and 2006 World Chess Olympiads is accordance with the regular USCF
rating system.

Motion Five: The office is hereby directed to purchase a three-chip
camdorder for use by the publications department to make videos of
events such as the National Elementary Championship for broadcast on
the USCF website, on youtube and other media for promotional purposes
and also to make and record videos of the USCF Delegates meeting and
Executive Board meetings. A SONY 2100 camcorder or equivalent at an
estimated cost of $2300 is recommended for this purpose.

Motion Six: Inasmuch as Myron and Rachel Lieberman have provided the
tapes of the August and November meetings of the USCF Executive Board
to the USCF Executive Director, and inasmuch as the Executive Director
has failed and refused to provide those tapes to Terry Vibbert for
uploading to the USCF website and inasmuch that this is in violation
of the bylaws and a delegate mandate requiring that either a tape or a
transcript of all Executive Board meetings be posted on the website,
the Executive Director is hereby censured for failing to provide those
taped and the office is hereby directed to provide those tapes to
Terry Vibbert or such other person for uploading onto the website. The
board also thanks Terry Vibbery for the great work he did in uploading
the tapes of all of the May meeting and most of the February meeting
onto the website.

Motion Seven: Resolved: The USCF hereby establishes the Irina Krush
Tournament of Girl Champions, which is to be held annually at the same
time and place as the US Open Chess Championship.

Motion Eight: Inasmush as at the meeting of the board held on August
14, 2006 it was reported by the Executive Director that all or almost
all of the financial records have been lost or destroyed, and inasmuch
as the Executive Director subsequently reported that some records have
been found in 125 storage boxes in a storage bin in Crossville,
Tennessee, and inasmuch as the Executive Director was teherupon
ordered by the VP of Finance to conduce an inventory of these storage
boxes and inasmuch as to this day the Executive Director has failed
and refused even to begin to conduct said inventory the Executive
Director is hereby censured.

Motion Nine: Resolved: The Board hereby thanks Tim Tobiason for
completing or nearly completing the difficult task of scanning and
making available to DVD all back issues of Chess Life newspaper from
1946 through 1960.

Please place the above motions on the agenda for the board meeting on
August 2, 2007.

Sam Sloan
