The following motions were voted at the EB meeting on August 02, 2007:

EB07 - 114 - Hall - The Executive Board adds Wayne Praeder to the
Forum Oversight committee. PASSED 4-1 with Sam Sloan opposed.

Bill Hall went offline at 11:16 AM. The &quot;Junior Tournament Membership&quot;
was then discussed.  Bill Goichberg offered the following motion:

EB07 - 115 - Goichberg - Tournament Memberships (TMs)will be revised
as follows: All adult TMs will cost $12, of which $10 can be applied
to a regular adult membership. Junior TMs, of which $5 may be applied
to a Young Adult, Youth, or Scholastic Membership. PASSED 4-1 with Sam
Sloan opposed.

Sam Sloan presented a number of motions for consideration

EB07 - 116 - Sloan - Resolved: Executive Director Bill Hall is hereby
censured and reprimanded for failing to provide documents to the Board
pertaining to the Pension / Profit Sharing Plan. TABLED 5-1 with Sam
Sloan opposed. on a motion by Don Schultz.

EB07 - 117 - Sloan - Inasmuch as Bobby Fischer is a USCF member by
Delegate mandate and a 1992 resolution submitted by Joe Lux, he is to
be assigned a USCF ID number and his name and last rating is to be
posted on the MSA section of the website as a USCF member. REFERRED to
the Top Players Committee 5-1 with Sam Sloan opposed on a motion by
Don Schultz.

EB07 - 118 - Sloan - Grandmaster Larry Evans is hereby reinstated as a
regular monthly columnist in &quot;Chess Life&quot; magazine. His regular
monthly question and answer column is hereby restored. The Editor of
&quot;Chess Life&quot; is hereby specifically ordered and directed to publish
said monthly column. FAILED 1-4-1 with Sam Sloan in favor and Beatriz
Marinello abstaining.

EB07 - 119 - Sloan - Resolved: It shall be the policy of the USCF to
rate (all players in) all World Championship events and all top level
super-Grandmaster events. The Ratings Department is hereby directed to
rate the 2004 and 2006 World Chess Olympiads in accordance with the
regular USCF rating system. FAILED 2-4 with Beatriz Marinello and Sam
Sloan in favor.

EB07-120 - Sloan - The office is hereby directed to purchase a three-
chip camcorder for use by the Publications Department to make videos
of events such as the National Elementary Championship for broadcast
on the USCF website, on YouTube and other media for promotional
purposes, and also to make and record videos of the USCF Delegates
meeings and Executive Board meetings. A SONY 2100 camcorder or
equivalent at an estimated cost of $2,300 is recommended for tis
purpose. REFERRED to the Executive Director 5-1 with Sam Sloan opposed
on a motion by Don Schultz.

EB07-121 - Sloan - Inasmuch as Myron and Rachel Lieberman have
provided the tapes of the August and November, 2006, meetings of the
USCF Executive Board to the USCF Executive Director, and inasmuch as
the Executive Director has failed and refused to provide these tapes
to Terry Vibbert for uploading to the USCF website (Please note: The
recordings are sent to the USCF office, not specifically to the
Executive Director.), and inasmuch as this is in violation of the
Bylaws and a Delegate mandate requiring that either a tape or a
transcript of all USCF Executive Board meetings be posted on the
website, the Executive Director is hereby censured for failing to
provide those tapes and the office is hereby directed to provide those
tapes to Terry Vibbert or such other person for uploading onto the
website. The Board also thanks Terry Vibbert for the great work he did
in uploading the tapes of the May meeting and most of the February
meeting onto the website. FAILED 1-4 with Sam Sloan in favor and Don
Schultz not present. Please note: Don Schultz did not return to the
meeting.

EB07-122 - Sloan - Resolved, the USCF hereby establishes the Irina
Krush Tournament of Girl Champions, which is to be held annually at
the same time and place as the US Open Chess Championship. FAILED 1-4
with Sam Sloan in favor.

EB07-123 - Sloan - Inasmuch as at the meeting of the Board held on
August 14, 2006, it was reported by the Executive Director that all or
almost all of the financial records have been lost or destroyed, and
inasmuch as the Executive Director subsequently reported that some
records have been found in 125 storage boxes in a storage bin in
Crossville, TN, and inasmuch as the Executive Director was thereupon
ordered by the VP of Finance to conduct an invenory of these storage
boxes and inasmuch as to this day the Executive Director has failed
and refused to even begin to conduct said inventory, the Executive
Director is hereby censured. FAILED 1-4 with Sam Sloan in favor.

EB07-124 - Sloan - The Board hereby thanks Tim Tobiason for competing
or nearly completing the difficult task of scanning and making
available on DVD all back issues of &quot;Chess Life&quot; newspaper from 1946
through 1960. PASSED 5-0.

EB07-125 - Goichberg - Rating Fees are increased as follows:

$.18 becomes $.25
$.20 becomes $.40
$.40 becomes $.60

PASSED 4-0 with Joel Channing not present.
